CCCXXXII. Grift to J ames Stewart, son to J ohnne Stewart servant to James Lord Down collector general, of the teinds of Mekill Dysart, formerly pertaining to the canons of Brechin, extending to thirty pounds Scots, lying within the sberiff- domof Forfar and vacant by the decease of Mr. Alexander Brysoun last donator thereof, and that for the said Jamcs' support at the schools for the space of seven years. Dated at Halieruidhous 24th December 1583.

CCCXXXIH. Tack for nineteen years to Robert Guthrie of Lwnane of the teinds of his lands of Ovir Dysart within the parish of Brechin, belonging formerly in com- mon to the canons of Brechin but since the reformation to the King, for yearly payment of ten pounds Scots. Dated at Halieruidhous 26th December 1583.

CCCXXXW. Tack for nineteen years to James Mailwill of Dysert of the teinds of Nethir Dysert otherwise called Mekill Dysert, lying and belonging as aforesaid, for yearly payment of twenty pounds Scots. Dated at Halieruidhous l7th Feb- ruary 1583.
